PepsiCo Gets Four-Year $2.88 Billion Revolving Credit Line

-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   I d z e l i s
-- 
2011-06-15T21:37:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/pepsico-gets-four-year-2-88-billion-revolving-credit-line-1-.html
PepsiCo Inc., the Purchase, New
York-based soda and snack company, has obtained a four-year,
$2.88 billion revolving  credit line .  PepsiCo said today in a regulatory filing that it may
increase the size of the new unsecured revolver to as much $3.5
billion, upon agreement with its lending group.  The biggest lenders on the credit line are  Citibank NA ,
JPMorgan Chase & Co. and Bank of America Corp., each with a
$325 million commitment, the document shows.  In a revolving credit facility, money can be borrowed again
